Silk
We get silk from silkw orm. A silkw orm feeds on the leaves of a mulberr y 
plan t. It mak es a home around itself with long sticky threads. 
This home is called a cocoon. The thread from cocoon is used to mak e silk 
threads. Silk threads are then woven to mak e silk cloth.Wool
We get wool from . Wool is actually the hair that grows on a sheep's sheep
body . The sheep's hair is cut and then washed. It is then dried. On drying, 
it becomes soft and clean. It is then spun into woollen threads. These 
threads ar e used t o knit s weaters, caps, sock s, muf flers and other w arm
